	                                <p>Hey again Diego!</p><p>Hmm. In short, it shouldn't lose its markup. Obviously, when you bubble an error, it will then show at the *top* of your form, when you call form_errors(form). However, the same markup should be used to render *those* errors as is used to render the errors for an individual field inside form_row(form.someField). However, if you form error styling relies on being inside some div that's rendered by "form_row", then you obviously won't have that markup when the fields are rendered globally.</p><p>In other words, this shouldn't happen. So, tell me more :)</p>
	                            </div>
